```sql
-- Deduplicate customer_channels to primary attribution (earliest per customer)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/mart/fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
-- Calculate customer revenue by attribution channel and store city
WITH transactions AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
),
channels AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }}
),
stores AS (
    SELECT
        store_id,
        city
    FROM {{ ref('stg_stores') }}
)
SELECT
    COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
    SUM(t.amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(t.transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions t
LEFT JOIN channels ch
    ON ch.customer_id = t.customer_id
LEFT JOIN stores s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)'),
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)')
